In [10]:
def value_counts(data, col, style=True):
    table = data[col].value_counts().rename_axis('Value').reset_index(name='Count')
    table['Percentage'] = table['Count'] / table['Count'].sum(axis=0)
    
    if style:
        table = table.style.format({'Count': '{:,}', 'Percentage': '{:.2%}'}).hide_index()
        
    return table

Melakukan grouping berdasarkan City_ID paling umum.

CTY06-023 dan CTY06-133 termasuk City ID paling umum maka akan masuk ke dalam grup 1, sedangkan ID yang lain masuk ke grup 0

In [44]:
CCI=[] 
for i,j in enumerate (data['City_ID']):
    if j=='CTY06-023':
        CCI.append(1)
    elif j=='CTY06-133':
        CCI.append(1)
    else:
        CCI.append(0)
data['Common_City']=CCI

Menambahkan feature peak months,days dan operational hours untuk menunjukkan transaksi paling banyak dilakukan pada bulan, dan hari apa. Untuk operational hours digunakan asumsi 10.00-22.00 adalah jam operasional merchant

In [49]:
MTH=[] 
for j in data['Month']:
    array= np.isin(months['Value'],j)
    if any(array)==True:
        MTH.append(1)
    elif all(array)==False:
        MTH.append(0)
data['Peak_Months']=MTH
In [50]:

    array= np.isin(days['Value'],j)
    if any(array)==True:
        DYS.append(1)
    elif all(array)==False:
        DYS.append(0)
data['Peak_Days']=DYS

Data Preparation¶

Untuk data yang kosong akan diisi dengan median variabel yang diinginkan berdasarkan variabel Common Merchant ID nya.

Untuk Minimum Average Transaction yang dibawah 1000 juga akan diisi dengan median dari Minimum Average Transaction berdasarkan Common Merchant ID yang dimiliki, karena Minimum Average Transaction <1000 dianggap outlier

Untuk transaction amount =1 juga diisi dengan median berdasarkan Common Merchant ID nya

In [38]:
def null_counts(data, style=True):
    nulls = data.isna().sum().rename_axis('Columns').reset_index(name='Count')
    nulls['Percentage'] = nulls['Count'] / len(data)
    nulls = nulls.loc[nulls['Count'] > 0]
    nulls.sort_values(by='Count', ascending=False, inplace=True)
    nulls.reset_index(drop=True, inplace=True)
    
    if style:
        nulls = nulls.style.format({'Count': '{:,}', 'Percentage': '{:.2%}'}).hide_index()
        
    return nulls

def median(var,status):
    med=data.loc[data['Common_Merchant_ID']==status,var].median()
    return(med)

In [60]:
from statsmodels.tools.tools import add_constant
from statsmodels.stats.outliers_influence import variance_inflation_factor

def vif(data, features, style=True):
    # Add constant to the GLM variables
    X = add_constant(data[features])
    vif_values = [variance_inflation_factor(X.values, i) for i in range(1, X.shape[1])]
    vif_df = pd.DataFrame({'Variable': features, 'VIF': vif_values})
    vif_df = vif_df.sort_values('VIF', ascending=False).reset_index(drop=True)
    vif_df.index += 1

    if style:
        vif_df = vif_df.style.format({'VIF': '{:,.2f}'})
        
    return vif_df

def target_boxplot(data, variable, target='Target', plotsize=(8, 8), colors=['green', 'red'], labels=['No', 'Yes'], limits=None):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=plotsize)
    
    bp = sns.boxplot(x=target, y=variable, data=data, showmeans=True, meanline=True, 
                     palette=colors, width=0.3,
                     flierprops=dict(marker='o', markerfacecolor='red', markeredgecolor='white', alpha=0.5),
                     meanprops=dict(linestyle='-', linewidth=2, color='orange'),
                     medianprops=dict(linestyle='-', linewidth=2, color='white'), 
                     boxprops=dict(linewidth=0, alpha=0.7))
    
    bp.set(xticklabels=labels, ylim=limits)
    
    plt.show()

In [74]:
def timer(start_time, header='\nProgram Schedule'):
    end_time = pd.to_datetime('now') + pd.Timedelta('07:00:00')
    print(header)
    print(start_time.strftime('Start   : %Y-%m-%d %I:%M:%S %p'))
    print(end_time.strftime('Finish  : %Y-%m-%d %I:%M:%S %p'))
    run_time = str(end_time - start_time)
    idx1 = run_time.find(' ', 3) + 1
    idx2 = run_time.find('.')
    print('Runtime :', run_time[idx1 : idx2], '\n')

from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split

start_time = pd.to_datetime('now') + pd.Timedelta('07:00:00')
trains = []
tests = []

for i in range(0,30):
    
    train, test = train_test_split(data2, test_size=0.25, stratify=data2[response])
    train = h2o.H2OFrame(train)
    test = h2o.H2OFrame(test)
    train[response] = train[response].asfactor()
    test[response] = test[response].asfactor()
    trains.append(train)
    tests.append(test)

timer(start_time, header='\nConverting DataFrame to H2O Frame')

def model_performance(model, threshold, train=False, valid=True, xval=False, header='Value', style=False):
    f1 = model.F1(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    precision = model.precision(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    sensitivity = model.recall(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    accuracy = model.accuracy(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    
    metrics = {'Threshold': threshold, 'F1': f1, 'Precision': precision, 'Sensitivity': sensitivity, 'Accuracy': accuracy}
    performance = pd.DataFrame(metrics.values(), columns=[header], index=metrics.keys())
    
    if style:
        performance = performance.style.format('{:.2%}')
        
    return performance

def variable_importances(model, limit=0.95):
    varimp = model.varimp(use_pandas=True)
    varimp['cumulative'] = varimp['percentage'].cumsum()
    varimp = varimp[varimp['cumulative'] <= limit].copy()
    
    return varimp

    threshold = model_gbm[i].leader.F1(train=False,valid=True,xval=False)[0][0]
    precision=model_gbm[i].leader.precision(train=False,valid=True,xval=False,thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    sensitivity=model_gbm[i].leader.sensitivity(train=False,valid=True,xval=False,thresholds=threshold)[0][1]

    precision_total.append(precision)

In [108]:



     


def model_performance(model, threshold, train=False, valid=True, xval=False, header='Value', style=False):
    f1 = model.F1(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    precision = model.precision(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    sensitivity = model.recall(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    accuracy = model.accuracy(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    
    metrics = {'Threshold': threshold, 'F1': f1, 'Precision': precision, 'Sensitivity': sensitivity, 'Accuracy': accuracy}
    performance = pd.DataFrame(metrics.values(), columns=[header], index=metrics.keys())
    
    if style:
        performance = performance.style.format('{:.2%}')
        
    return performance

In [194]:



     


f1_total=[]
threshold_total=[]
precision_total=[]
sensitivity_total=[]
accuracy_total=[]
var_glm=[]

for i in range (30):
    f1=model_glm[i].leader.F1(train=False,valid=True,xval=False)[0][1]
    threshold = model_glm[i].leader.F1(train=False,valid=True,xval=False)[0][0]
    precision=model_glm[i].leader.precision(train=False,valid=True,xval=False,thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    sensitivity=model_glm[i].leader.sensitivity(train=False,valid=True,xval=False,thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    accuracy=model_glm[i].leader.accuracy(train=False,valid=True,xval=False,thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    
    f1_total.append(f1)
    threshold_total.append(threshold)
    precision_total.append(precision)
    sensitivity_total.append(sensitivity)
    accuracy_total.append(accuracy)
    
    vars = variable_importances(model_glm[i].leader,limit=1)
    var_glm.append(vars)

In [120]:



     


def model_performance(model, threshold, train=False, valid=True, xval=False, header='Value', style=False):
    f1 = model.F1(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    precision = model.precision(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    sensitivity = model.recall(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    accuracy = model.accuracy(train=train, valid=valid, xval=xval, thresholds=threshold)[0][1]
    
    metrics = {'Threshold': threshold, 'F1': f1, 'Precision': precision, 'Sensitivity': sensitivity, 'Accuracy': accuracy}
    performance = pd.DataFrame(metrics.values(), columns=[header], index=metrics.keys())
    
    if style:
        performance = performance.style.format('{:.2%}')
        
    return performance

AB Testing GBM and GLM¶










In [238]:



     


controls=gbm['F1']



     















In [239]:



     


targeteds=glm['F1']



     















In [240]:



     


from scipy.stats import wilcoxon

simulations = 1000
alpha = 0.05
pvals = []

start_time = pd.to_datetime('now') + pd.Timedelta('07:00:00')

for simulation in range(simulations):
    model1 = np.random.choice(controls, len(controls))
    model2 = np.random.choice(targeteds, len(targeteds))
    
    w, p = wilcoxon(model1,model2)
    pvals.append(p)

power = np.mean(np.array(pvals) < alpha)
print('Power Level:', str(power))
timer(start_time, header='\nSimulation')

from scipy.stats import wilcoxon

simulations = 1000
alpha = 0.05
pvals = []

start_time = pd.to_datetime('now') + pd.Timedelta('07:00:00')

for simulation in range(simulations):
    model1 = np.random.choice(controls, 100)
    model2 = np.random.choice(targeteds, 100)

    w, p = wilcoxon(model1,model2)
    pvals.append(p)

power = np.mean(np.array(pvals) < alpha)
print('Power Level:', str(power))
timer(start_time, header='\nSimulation')

In [232]:



     


from scipy.stats import wilcoxon

simulations = 1000
alpha = 0.05
pvals = []

start_time = pd.to_datetime('now') + pd.Timedelta('07:00:00')

for simulation in range(simulations):
    model1 = np.random.choice(controls, len(controls))
    model2 = np.random.choice(targeteds, len(targeteds))

    w, p = wilcoxon(model1,model2)
    pvals.append(p)

power = np.mean(np.array(pvals) < alpha)
print('Power Level:', str(power))
timer(start_time, header='\nSimulation')



     


















    
    






Power Level: 1.0

Runtime : 00:00:04

benefit=[]
loss=[]
for j in range (len (prediction)):
    tester_eval[j]['predicted']=prediction[j]['predict']
    df_test=pd.DataFrame(tester_eval[j].groupby(['predicted','Fraud_Status'])['Transaction_Amount'].sum())
    df_test.reset_index(inplace=True)
    benefit.append(df_test.loc[(df_test['Fraud_Status']==1)&(df_test['predicted']==1),'Transaction_Amount'].sum())
    loss.append(df_test.loc[df_test['Fraud_Status']==1,'Transaction_Amount'].sum())
